    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Are marquise engagement rings still in style?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Marquise engagement rings have returned to attention because they feel distinctive, flattering, and more expressive than standard round styles. They also fit the wider movement toward vintage-inspired and design-led rings.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do marquise diamonds look bigger than other shapes?</h3>
        <p>They often appear larger than many people expect because the elongated outline creates strong finger coverage and visual spread.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Who suits a marquise engagement ring best?</h3>
        <p>It often suits people who like elegant, elongated shapes, a slightly vintage mood, and rings that make the fingers appear longer and slimmer.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is a marquise engagement ring practical for everyday wear?</h3>
        <p>It can be, but the pointed tips need protection. A thoughtful setting and well-made prongs matter more with marquise stones than many buyers realize.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What ratio looks best in a marquise diamond?</h3>
        <p>There is no single perfect ratio. Shorter marquise stones feel softer and broader, while longer ones feel sharper and more dramatic. The best choice depends on the overall mood you want.</p>
      </div>
